## Correctness
The groove implementation is present and aligns with most acceptance points:
- New "'`GrooveProfile` model and helpers implement swing/shuffle-like ratio pairs, push/pull offsets, microtiming determinism, polyrhythm masks, polymeter phase, and entrainment metadata.
- Tracker scene building now stamps groove metadata onto `TrackerScene.metadata` and each `TrackerStep.metadata`.
- Deterministic behavior is preserved in scheduler: runtime ordering is still sorted by `(row, lane, frequency)` and metadata is carried as opaque step payload.
- `pytest tests/ -x` completed with all tests passing (`1947 passed`).

Not fully implemented yet: body/room-pulse entrainment is available as metadata but not threaded into `build_scene_from_score` from scene metadata, so runtime does not currently reflect entrainment inputs in tempo/IOI decisions.

## Completeness
Most acceptance coverage is present and newly added tests exercise required areas:
- IOI ratios: `swing_ioi_pair` + `apply_groove_to_ioi` unit tests.
- Swing offsets: ratio positioning tests (`groove_swing_ratio`, `groove_swing_position`) and ratio order assertions.
- Phrase breath points: `breath_points_for_phrase` and `groove_breath` coverage.
- Section-specific groove identity: metadata assertions and `groove_for_section` priority tests.
- Polyrhythm/polymeter/entrainment helpers and metadata all have unit tests in the new file.

The only notable gap is entrainment propagation from score/runtime inputs into live scheduling (not yet wired).

## Consistency
Changes are consistent with existing architecture:
- Pure stdlib implementation under `senseweave`.
- Tracker changes only extend metadata and do not alter scheduling control flow.
- Type patterns and metadata string convention match existing runtime patterns.
- Tests are placed in task-specific file with class-based layout and local path sys.path setup consistent with nearby unit tests.

## Security
No new network, file-system, or command execution risks were introduced in this commit.
No secrets are emitted in groove metadata. Security posture appears unchanged.

## Quality
Code is coherent and readable, with clear docstrings and focused helper extraction.
Test suite quality is high with direct unit coverage and tracker metadata integration assertions.
One maintainability note: `music_tracker.py` currently ignores entrainment inputs even though the groove model supports them; this is the primary integration seam to finish.

